ue,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":false,"has_discussions":false,"forks_count":4451,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":726,"license":{"key":"other","name":"Other","spdx_id":"NOASSERTION","url":null,"node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTA="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["automation","ruby","vagrant","virtualization"],"visibility":"public","forks":4451,"open_issues":726,"watchers":27088,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"Before calling change_host_name:\n\n/etc/hostname:\n\n```\nlocalhost\n```\n\n/etc/hosts:\n\n```\n127.0.0.1       localhost\n```\n\nAfter calling change_host_name:\n\n/etc/hostname:\n\n```\nnewhostname\n```\n\n/etc/hosts:\n\n```\n127.0.0.1 newhostname.fqdn.com newhostname\n```\n\nWhat we want instead for the new state of /etc/hosts is something more like:\n\n```\n127.0.0.1 localhost\n127.0.1.1 newhostname.fqdn.com newhostname\n```\n\nThis could be a common scenario for a VM template that doesn't know what its eventual hostname will be, and so starts out with the name 'localhost' (this is what I am currently working with).\n\nWhen `change_host_name` is run, `@current_hostname` is set to the initial value in `/etc/hostname`. Later, when `update_etc_hosts` is run, that initial value is used in a search and replace in `/etc/hosts`. The comment on the `update_etc_hosts` method shows the intent:\n\n```\n        # /etc/hosts should resemble:\n        #127.0.0.1   localhost\n        #127.0.1.1   host.fqdn.com host.fqdn host\n```\n\nThe authors and users of `update_etc_hosts` are expecting the second line to get updated or added but in this case we end up modifying the first line instead, destroying the association between `localhost` and the loopback address, which is almost certainly not what we intended.\n\nLikely a related issue with the Fedora plugin, but that is another plugin so I don't consider it part of this issue: https://github.com/mitchellh/vagrant/issues/6202\n\nRelated discussion on StackOverflow (also Fedora): http://stackoverflow.com/questions/33117939/vagrant-do-not-map-hostname-to-loopback-address-in-etc-hosts\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/issues/6446/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/issues/6446/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":458020400,"node_id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDQ1ODAyMDQwMA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/issues/events/458020400","actor":{"login":"sethvargo","id":408570,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwODU3MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/408570?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo","html_url":"https://github.com/sethvargo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sethvargo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"labeled","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2015-11-07T23:21:15Z","label":{"name":"bug","color":"e11d21"},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"id":458020401,"node_id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDQ1ODAyMDQwMQ==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/issues/ev